LinearRegression

Szabolcs Stremler

December 27, 2017

Initialization

set.seed(0)

# generate data with r = 0.8 correlation
N <- 30
X <- data.frame(matrix(rnorm(N, mean=0, sd=1), N, 1))
r <- 0.5
X[,2] <- r*X[,1] + rnorm(length(X[,1]), mean=0, sd=sqrt(1 - r^2))
colnames(X) <- c('x', 'y')
cor(X[,1], X[,2])
## [1] 0.4667734

Train

linReg <- LinearRegression$new()
weight <- linReg$train(X[,1], X[,2], eta = 0.01, maxit = 15)
print(weight)
##                b        X
## [1,] -0.02189472 0.506567

Plot steps

linReg$plotAnimation()

Plot trajectory

linReg$plotTrajectoryAnimation()
